THREE doctors have been shot and seriously injured during a robbery at Letaba Hospital doctors' residence in the early hours of Thursday morning. According to the Limpopo Health Department the conditions surrounding the robbery are still sketchy. However, it is understood that 5 heavily armed men broke into the residence and robbed tenants of their belongings and shot three in the process. The MEC for Health in the province, Dr Phophi Ramathuba is on the way to visit the hospital this morning. Ramathuba says she is concerned about the impact of increasing violent crimes on service delivery at rural hospitals and clinics across Limpopo. 